properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued February 29 at 10:14PM PST until March 1 at 9:00AM PST by NWS Los Angeles/Oxnard CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Northwest to north winds 20 to 30 mph with gusts up to
45 mph, strongest through passes and canyons. Local gusts to 50
mph possible.

* WHERE...Santa Barbara County Mountains.

* WHEN...Until 9 AM PST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Gusty winds will make driving difficult and could
blow around unsecured objects. Tree limbs could be blown down
and a few power outages may result.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...This includes Highways 101, 154 and
192...as well as the Gaviota and San Marcos Passes.
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 9 AM PST SUNDAY
